               <p>SOLOMON WORMS. I am a <rs id="t18301209-240-viclabel1352" type="occupation">broker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-240-victim2019 t18301209-240-viclabel1352"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18301209-240-crimeloc1353">Queen-street, St. Giles'</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-240-crimeloc1353" type="placeName" value="Queen-street, St. Giles'"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-240-crimeloc1353" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-240-off1350 t18301209-240-crimeloc1353"></join>. On the 11th of December this looking-glass was outside my window, which was not open; I had a lad there to mind the things - an opposite neighbour's lad hallooed out; I ran out, and saw the looking-glass in the road, opposite my door - it was mine; I had seen it safe five minutes before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-240-person2020">
                  JAMES 
                  KING
               <interp inst="t18301209-240-person2020" type="surname" value="KING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-240-person2020" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-240-person2020" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am twelve years old, and live with my brother, who is a broker, opposite Mr. Worms'. I was looking across just at dusk, and saw Worms' lad talking to two other boys; the big boy gave Worms' boy a piece of sweet-stuff - I saw the prisoner take the glass off the door, and walk away with it; I ran over and caught him - he then dropped it, and said, "Let me go;" I called to Worms, who came out, took the glass up, and claimed it; I had seen the prisoner before, I did not know who he was.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-240-person2021">
                  JOSEPH 
                  TINDALL
               <interp inst="t18301209-240-person2021" type="surname" value="TINDALL"></interp>
